Series.Actors: |Aaron Stanford|Amanda Schull|Kirk Acevedo|Barbara Sukowa|Todd Stashwick|Emily Hampshire|Noah Bean|Tom Noonan|
Series.Overview: The show follows the journey of a time traveler, Cole, from the post-apocalyptic future. Using a dangerous and untested method of time travel, Cole arrives in the present day on a mission to locate and eradicate the source of a deadly plague that will eventually decimate 93.6% of the human race.

Episode.Overview: Project Splinter is about to begin. Will the future be erased by changing the past?
Is Project Splinter a failure or a success?
Jennifer Goines and the number 12 are a bad combination.

Episode.EpisodeName: Out of Time: Enemy at the Gates
Episode.Overview: Is everyone in danger - from something other than the virus?
That's all it takes before we are out of time.
Something with the timeline is wrong. Very wrong.
The past may hold the key to the future.
What’s the best way to celebrate the end of existence?
The future of the mission - really, the future of the future - is up in the air.
A team member leaves a last message.
Leland Goines has an empire to protect.

Episode.EpisodeName: Out of Time: The Next Cycle
Episode.Overview: When time is broken, it just needs a little help.
Jennifer Goines interviews a potential assistant. Guess how that goes.

Episode.EpisodeName: Out of Time: Names to Learn
Episode.Overview: The old Markridge is dead. Long live Jennifer Goines.
Flash forward later in Season 2: Why is Dr. Jones all alone? Where did everyone go?
Jennifer Goines has a few things to say about the end of the world. But what’s truth, and what’s her crazy?
The Witness brings salvation, or destruction. It’s all a matter of perspective – and time.

Episode.GuestStars: |Ramon De Ocampo|Robert Wisdom|Zeljko Ivanek|Bill Timoney|Mark Boyd|ShaTyrah Dexter|Harry Wetzel|Julie Sifuentes Etheridge|
Episode.Overview: 27 years after a virus wipes out most of humanity, scientists send James Cole back to 2015 to stop the plague from ever happening. Cole's only lead is virologist Dr. Cassandra Railly, who knows the dangerous source of the outbreak.

Episode.GuestStars: |Sam Kalilieh|Murray Furrow|Philip Yang|Daniel Park|Joanne Reece|Miguel Anthony|Jee-Yun Lee|
Episode.Overview: The trail of a mysterious organization called the “Army of the 12 Monkeys” leads Cole to a mental institution in 2015, where a patient holds the key to the plague that destroys the world. Meanwhile, despite warnings that her involvement may disrupt the course of history, Dr. Railly risks her life to help him.
Cole's search for the location of the virus leads him to 2014, and to a devastating moment in Dr. Railly's life involving a dangerous outbreak in Haiti.
A fight for the future ensues when a dangerous band of marauders hunting for Cole and Ramse threatens the mission to save the past.
Cole and Dr. Railly face off with the Army of the 12 Monkeys when both discover the Night Room – an off-site, black ops lab that houses the virus that will one day destroy the world.
When the tragic events of the Night Room create an alternate reality in 2043, Cole risks his future.
Cole, Dr. Railly and Aaron strive to stop the virus from being deployed as a bio-weapon in Chechnya.
The Core that powers the time machine is fading. To get Cole back from the past, Jones must convince her former colleagues at the military operation "Spearhead" that her mission is worth saving.
Cole finds himself in 2017 at the height of the plague. Out of options, Jones faces an impossible choice to replace the Core.
Forces come to a head when Ramse does what it takes to protect his newfound family, leaving Cole to deal with the aftermath.
Cole splinters to Tokyo, 1987 in a last chance effort to stop the Army of the 12 Monkeys.

Episode.GuestStars: |Barbara Sukowa|Emily Hampshire|Todd Stashwick|Mark Margolis|Patrick Garrow|Demore Barnes|Alisen Down|Tom Noonan|
Episode.Overview: With Cole dying from the effects of time-travel, Railly must find the one person who can save him.

Episode.GuestStars: |Barbara Sukowa|Emily Hampshire|Todd Stashwick|Peter Outerbridge|Demore Barnes|Alisen Down|
Episode.Overview: Cole and Railly attempt a final confrontation with their closest enemies, while Jones faces a new threat to all that she's accomplished.
Cole and Ramse repair their broken friendship while on the run; Railly and Jones navigate an uncertain future in 2043.

When an attempt to destroy the virus changes the future, Cole finds himself stranded in 2016 with an unstable Jennifer Goines, who may or may not be his key to getting home. Meanwhile, Jones and Railly must deal with both the consequences of the changed timeline and the temporal facility's newest prisoner -- Ramse.
Despite the growing tension between them, Cole and Cassie time travel to New York during World War II to track down a dangerous member of the Twelve.
Jones turns to Ramse for help getting Cole and Cassie back from 1944; Jones visits old Jennifer Goines to explore the true nature of time.
In the present, Cassie and Jennifer Goines run from the 12 Monkeys; in 2044, Cole and Ramse face off against Deacon.
Cole and Ramse travel to 1970s New York City to prevent the Twelve from murdering a Vietnam veteran with a connection to the Witness.
